Well, don't let me stop you.

That review of "The River Wall" was more vicious than it had to be.

If the play's crap, it's crap. No need to sugar coat it.

I think this place is a drug den. Or it used to be.

A hiding place for lost souls. Seems right up our alley.

I've never seen a ghost so scared.

Don't remind me. Jeeze.

We couldn't save George Ostin, but we can stop it from happening to anybody else.

With pleasure.

