Not yet.

It's just as well you can't get in. The stairwell is half-collapsed.

I'm not standing out here in the cold. Is there anything that can help get me inside?

Maybe. I'll go back in and look around some more.

The lobby's a mess. The stairwell is even worse.

Anything that can help me get this door open?

As urban graffiti goes, I've definitely seen better.

I didn't know you were such an expert.

I've seen my fair share. But words written on bricks? What a waste of paint.

I'm freezing out here. You think it's any warmer inside?

It's not exactly inviting, but we'll get you in. There's got to be a way. 

I'm sure the answer is right in front of us.

Since you're inside anyway, how about you look around? Maybe there's something useful.

Like what? The used needles, the dirty mattress, or the fallen bits of ceiling?

Don't get snippy, darling.

Did you see anything useful when you were wandering around?

Who knows what's useful and what's not?

Physical objects are your gig, sweetheart. You got hands. Use 'em.

Why'd you pick up that fuse, anyway?

